00:36:10,700 --> 00:36:13,580
We treated him with gentamicin when we thought it was bacterial,

544
00:36:13,580 --> 00:36:15,660
<i>which means the dose of amphotericin b we'll need</i>

545
00:36:15,660 --> 00:36:18,880
to cure him will probably leave him deaf.

546
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:21,440
Sorry, I stopped listening after you said

547
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:24,090
<i>"the dose we'll need to cure him. "</i>

548
00:36:33,410 --> 00:36:36,260
Blind and deaf?

549
00:36:37,210 --> 00:36:39,130
I'd rather be dead.

550
00:36:40,660 --> 00:36:41,930
You will be.

551
00:36:44,920 --> 00:36:46,620
I can live with that.

552
00:36:50,820 --> 00:36:52,840
You never did get my humor.

553
00:36:56,030 --> 00:36:59,460
There's a chance your hearing won't be completely gone.

554
00:37:02,790 --> 00:37:04,570
How much of a chance?

555
00:37:06,610 --> 00:37:08,060
A small one.

556
00:37:08,580 --> 00:37:10,200
<i>But a chance.</i>

557
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:21,540
I'm-I'm refusing treatment.

558
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:26,870
You don't know how hard things are already for me.

559
00:37:29,700 --> 00:37:31,630
I can't handle any more.

560
00:37:36,260 --> 00:37:37,590
I can't.

561
00:37:46,070 --> 00:37:47,950
I'm here to apologize.

562
00:37:48,700 --> 00:37:51,330
<i>I could have handled the news with more...</i>

563
00:37:52,630 --> 00:37:53,710
Aplomb?

564
00:37:56,130 --> 00:37:59,480
I have a son. That's great news.

565
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:02,670
What else did she tell you to say?

566
00:38:02,670 --> 00:38:05,610
You're not a lunatic, you're not a mistake.

567
00:38:09,660 --> 00:38:13,570
<i>I never liked your friend... My father.</i>

568
00:38:13,570 --> 00:38:16,830
Well, he could be a bit intense at times.

569
00:38:16,830 --> 00:38:20,820
But unlike you, I did respect him.

570
00:38:23,350 --> 00:38:25,200
Do you respect your mother?

571
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:30,910
Well, we do have that in common.

572
00:38:30,910 --> 00:38:32,820
And we all love her.

573
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:37,070
So we don't have much choice, do we?

574
00:38:40,010 --> 00:38:43,310
Son, see you at dinner.

575
00:39:00,420 --> 00:39:01,850
Will, it's me.

576
00:39:05,130 --> 00:39:06,630
Let me guess.

577
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:11,140
The doctor who thinks I'm an ass
wants you to convince me to live.

578
00:39:12,430 --> 00:39:13,720
Yes.

579
00:39:18,930 --> 00:39:20,100
It won't work.

580
00:39:21,690 --> 00:39:22,990
I KNOW.

581
00:39:24,860 --> 00:39:26,360
So I won't.

582
00:39:29,550 --> 00:39:32,430
Wow. You're that angry?

583
00:39:32,900 --> 00:39:35,360
I've made enough decisions for you.

584
00:39:37,700 --> 00:39:39,150
This is your life.

585
00:39:42,420 --> 00:39:43,990
Why'd you come back?

586
00:39:47,280 --> 00:39:49,040
Because I love you.

587
00:39:52,260 --> 00:39:55,680
And I want to be with you for as long as I can.

588
00:39:59,330 --> 00:40:01,330
Melissa, I'm so scared.

589
00:40:03,410 --> 00:40:04,600
Me too.

590
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:12,580
I'll always love you.

591
00:40:16,910 --> 00:40:18,710
Even if I was deaf?

592
00:40:20,620 --> 00:40:22,350
Even if anything.

593
00:40:41,050 --> 00:40:42,380
Is it working?

594
00:40:43,090 --> 00:40:44,290
He's still very ill,

595
00:40:44,290 --> 00:40:47,730
but if he keeps responding the way he has been,

596
00:40:47,730 --> 00:40:49,310
he should be fine.

597
00:40:50,950 --> 00:40:54,350
And his hearing? It's gone.

598
00:40:54,350 --> 00:40:56,940
<i>We don't know yet if it'll be permanent.</i>

599
00:41:05,580 --> 00:41:08,620
Melissa? Is that you?

600
00:41:08,620 --> 00:41:12,490
We've been squeezing his hand, once for yes, twice for no.

601
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:20,140
Can I ask you something?

602
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:24,360
I completely understand if you squeeze no.

603
00:41:31,770 --> 00:41:33,110
Will you marry me?

604
00:41:43,300 --> 00:41:46,070
Don't leave me hanging, now. Yes.

605
00:41:47,010 --> 00:41:49,120
Yes! Of course, yes!

606
00:41:49,120 --> 00:41:52,850
I- I heard that. You said yes, right?

607
00:41:52,850 --> 00:41:54,420
Yes! You said y-

608
00:42:05,130 --> 00:42:07,440
How long are you gonna wait until you tell me?

609
00:42:07,440 --> 00:42:11,010
I thought we already had the Santa Claus talk.

610
00:42:11,800 --> 00:42:15,100
You don't think I saw you steal Thomas' fork from the restaurant?

611
00:42:15,100 --> 00:42:17,620
 Why would I do that? For his DNA.

612
00:42:18,690 --> 00:42:21,890
That's... That's...

613
00:42:23,940 --> 00:42:25,320
